Returns the grid row that corresponds to the logical \fIy\fR\& coordinate\&.
.LP
The parameter \fIgridWindow\fR\& is new since wxWidgets 3\&.1\&.3\&. If it is specified, i\&.e\&. non-NULL, only the cells of this window are considered, i\&.e\&. the function returns \fIwxNOT_FOUND\fR\& if \fIy\fR\& is out of bounds\&.
.LP
If \fIgridWindow\fR\& is NULL, the function returns \fIwxNOT_FOUND\fR\& only if there is no row at all at the \fIy\fR\& position\&.
